[[div class="pseudomain"]]
The concept is simple — every entrant will submit one of their drafts to an organizer, and on the 17th of March, those drafts will be shuffled and redistributed — everyone will have 24 days until closing to work on that draft to the best of their ability. The event is being run by [[*user Uncle Nicolini]] and [[*user Queerious]]. To make things perfectly clear, this is an [https://discord.com/invite/scp Official SCP Discord Writing Channel] event, not a wiki contest! 
[[/div]]

[[div class="banner"]]
[[span class="greent"]]THE[[/span]] RULES
[[/div]]

[[div class="pseudomain"]]
**HARD RULES**
* All entrants are required to have at least one article posted with a rating greater than +10.
 * Exceptions can be made for the above, please ask an organizer about it.
* You are only allowed to submit one draft. Make it count.
 * Only links to wikidot sandboxes will be accepted. No notepads, no Google docs, no exceptions.
* Once you receive your assigned draft, it is considered your own. You may add, subtract, change, or otherwise affect the entire article at your discretion.
 * Keep in mind that your submitted draft may be changed in ways you do not expect. This is an intentional aspect of this event.
* Submit your draft to the organizers and/or post by the end of the event.

**RECOMMENDATIONS**
* You are not required to have a final polished draft submitted at the end of the writing phase; you simply need to produce something that can be read fully and critiqued. Use common sense.
 * You are allowed to continue polishing the draft and/or post it after the contest.
 * You are allowed to show your draft progress to others; this isn't art exchange!
* This is not a competition! This is a community event, so the real treasure are the friends we made along the way.
* We reserve the right to litigate nonsense and foolishness.
[[/div]]

